narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would say Italian 120 is a good course, but I would probably recommend that students apply to take it in Siena because they would get more speaking practice and have it concentrated within 8 weeks instead of every day.
I highly recommend the class. Great way to continue the language and the understanding of the culture.
You have to take L2 if you took L1 - simple as that. Just shop around for a good section!
It's just part two of L1: exactly what you'd expect. There are a couple of movies in class. Be prepared to work on more complex grammar concepts than in L1.
